                    <br />

                    <span style="{!IF(NOT(Opportunity.Account.BillingCountry == 'United States'), 'page-break-inside:avoid;', 'display:none;')}">
                        <apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Account.BillingCountry}" rendered="{!NOT(Opportunity.Account.BillingCountry == 'United States')}"
                        />
                        <br />
                    </span>
                    <apex:outputText value="{!'Attention: ' & Opportunity.Primary_Contact__c } " /> ("
                    <strong>Sponsor</strong>")  
                </p>
               
                <p style="font-family: Times; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.3;  page-break-inside:avoid;">
                   <apex:outputText value=" ${0,number} Loan Proposal to the acquisition an  an {1,number}-property [portfolio] located {2}">
                        <apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Loan_Size__c}" />
                        <apex:param value="{!IF(Opportunity.Number_of_Properties__c != null && Opportunity.Number_of_Properties__c > 1, allProperties[0].Number_of_Units__c, 0)}" />
                        <apex:param value="{!IF(Opportunity.Number_of_Properties__c != null && Opportunity.Number_of_Properties__c > 1, 'in ' + allProperties[0].City__c + ', ' + allProperties[0].State__c, 'at ' + allProperties[0].Name + ' ' + allProperties[0].City__c + ', ' + allProperties[0].State__c)}" />
                    </apex:outputText> (the "Property")
                </p>
                <p style="font-family: Times; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.3;  page-break-inside:avoid;">
                    <apex:outputText value="{! 'Dear ' & Opportunity.Contact__r.FirstName}" />:
                </p>

                <p class="paragraph">
                    CoreVest American Finance Lender LLC or an affiliated entity ("
                    <strong>Lender</strong>") is pleased to present this summary proposal to provide a secured line of credit for
                    the purchase and financing of eligible residential properties. As further set forth below, this proposal
                    is for discussion purposes only and is neither an expressed nor implied commitment to provide any financing
                    or to provide or purchase any loans or securities in connection with the transactions contemplated hereby.
                </p>
                
                                <table style="table-layout: fixed; width:95vw;" cellspacing="0">
                    <colgroup>
                        <col class="short" />
                        <col class="long" />
                    </colgroup>

                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Borrower:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         A bankruptcy-remote, Delaware single-purpose limited liability company ("the LLC") acceptable to Lender.  The LLC will include <apex:outputText value="{!' ' & Opportunity.Contact__r.Name}" /> ("Sponsor") or an affiliate of Sponsor approved by Lender as an equity owner and as managing member or manager.  Lender reserves the right to approve any other equity owners and/or managers in the LLC prior to closing, and no transfers, pledges or assignments of direct or indirect equity interests shall be permitted.  Borrower shall be prohibited from engaging in any other business activities and shall otherwise meet applicable rating agency criteria with respect to qualifying as a bankruptcy remote entity, including, but not limited to, the existence of 
                         <span style="background-color: #FFFF00">[one (1) independent manager and springing member - FOR LOANS > $20MM],  [two (2) independent managers and springing member - FOR LOANS > $50MM].</span>
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                       <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Guarantor:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         The undersigned "Sponsor", on a joint and several basis, and/or such individuals or entities acceptable to Lender following due diligence.
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Pledgor:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         A bankruptcy remote, Delaware single purpose limited liability company, acceptable to Lender following due diligence, which shall be the sole member of Borrower. Pledgor shall be prohibited from engaging in any other business activities and shall otherwise meet applicable rating agency criteria with respect to qualifying as a bankruptcy remote entity, including, but not limited to, the existence of one (1) independent manager and springing member.
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Net Worth and
                            Liquidity 
                            Requirement:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         Prior to Loan closing, Guarantor shall evidence a minimum net worth of not less than 100% of the Loan Amount and minimum cash liquidity of not less than 10% of the Loan Amount based on readily marketable securities and bank accounts within the United States of America.  Following Loan closing these requirements must be maintained at all times and shall be tested quarterly based on unaudited compiled financial statements with supporting bank account statements.
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Property:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         Existing <!--<apex:outputText value="{!Property.Name}" />-->property located in <apex:outputText value="{!allProperties[0].City__c}" />, <apex:outputText value="{!allProperties[0].State__c}" />, comprised of <span style="background-color: #FFFF00"><apex:outputText value="{0,number}"><apex:param value="{!allProperties[0].Number_of_Units__c}"/></apex:outputText></span> residential units (each, a "Residential Unit") and <span style="background-color: #FFFF00">[X]</span> Commercial units (each, a "Commercial Unit")]. No portion of the Property may at any time be occupied by Borrower, Guarantor or any interest owner, or affiliate or relative thereof.
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Loan Purpose:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         Acquisition and renovation of the Property.
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Closing:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         Anticipated to be sixty (60) days from the execution of this Loan Proposal (provided timely delivery of Due Diligence).
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr>
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Loan Amount:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                        <p>
                        Maximum Loan Amount of <apex:outputText value=" ${0,number} "><apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Loan_Size__c}" /></apex:outputText> , subject to confirmation and determined by Lender as follows: the Maximum Allocated Loan Amount will be the lesser of: 
                        (a) <apex:outputText value="{0,number,0}%">
    <apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Requested_LTV_Max__c}"/></apex:outputText>
 of the <strong>"As-Stabilized"</strong> market value of the Property as determined by Lender based on an appraisal of the Property prepared by an appraiser selected by Lender and in form and scope acceptable to Lender ("As-Stabilized Value") ;
 (b) <apex:outputText value="{0,number,0}%">
    <apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Requested_LTC_Max__c}"/></apex:outputText> of (i) the purchase price paid for the Property as determined by Lender plus (ii) the eligible project costs necessary to achieve Completion of the Improvements on the Property plus operating expenses and the Interest Allocation discussed below as set forth in the Budget approved by Lender prior to Loan closing ("Eligible Project Costs") and as more fully described in the loan documents and (c) the ‘as-is' debt yield shall be no less than <span class="mark">[  ]</span>% defined as ratio of annualized underwritten net cash flow as determined by Lender.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        The initial advance is anticipated to be the lesser of; 
                        (a) <span style="background-color: #FFFF00">$[x]</span>; 
                        (b) <apex:outputText value="{0,number,0}%">
    <apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Requested_LTV_Max__c}"/></apex:outputText> of Eligible Project Costs and 
    (c) <apex:outputText value="{0,number,0}%">
    <apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Requested_LTC_Max__c}"/></apex:outputText> of the "As-Is" appraised value as determined by Lender based on the appraisal of the Property prepared by an appraiser selected by Lender and in form and scope acceptable to Lender (<strong>"As-Is Value"</strong>) (<strong>"Initial Advance"</strong>). The remaining portion of the Maximum Loan Amount for the Property (the <strong>"Renovation Loan Proceeds"</strong>) will be advanced in multiple advances (each an <strong>"Advance"</strong>) to pay for Eligible Project Costs per the Lender approved Budget. Upon Borrower's request and upon satisfaction of certain requirements as detailed in the Loan Documents, which may include, without limitation, Lender's approval of renovation draws, Lender's review and approval of and inspection of engineer's site observation reports, Lender will advance funds from the Renovation Loan Proceeds to Borrower (but not more often than once per calendar month) to reimburse Borrower or pay approved third parties. The Renovation Loan Proceeds are estimated to be <span style="background-color: #FFFF00">$[x]</span> subject to confirmation by Lender. See Exhibit A - "Sources and Uses.  After 24 months, any unadvanced Renovation Loan Proceeds funds may be advanced by Lender, in Lender's sole and absolute discretion, into a Lender controlled escrow account for future disbursement.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        Lender shall determine minimum Property performance metrics (the "Minimum Renovation Performance") during underwriting and in consideration with Borrower's business plan. Lender will not be obligated to release Renovation Loan Proceeds to Borrower if Borrower fails to maintain the Minimum Renovation Performance, and/or upon the occurrence and continuation of a Cash Management Trigger Period. 
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        At all times until completion of the Renovation work, Borrower and Guarantor shall be required to keep the Loan "in balance". The Loan shall be deemed to be in balance only when the sum of the undisbursed Loan proceeds plus any equity contributions equals or exceeds the amount necessary to complete the Renovation work.
                        </p>
                        
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Borrower
                            Equity Contribution:
                        </td>
                         <!-- <td class="row-description">
                         $<span class="mark">[     ]</span> of invested equity capital to be evidenced at Loan closing (<strong>"Borrower Equity Contribution"</strong>), subject to confirmation as determined by Lender prior to Loan Closing based on the appraisal.
                         </td> -->
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Loan Term:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         <apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.LOC_Term__c}"/> (<strong>"Stated Maturity Date"</strong>).
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                           Extension Options:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         <span class="mark">[One / Two], [  ]</span>-month extension option(s) subject to extension requirements below. During the extension options, the monthly debt service payment will include principal and interest payments based upon a 30-year amortization schedule.
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                           Interest Rate:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         <p>The Loan will bear interest at a floating rate per annum equal to Term SOFR plus the&nbsp;<apex:outputText value="{0,number,0}%"><apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Requested_Index_Margin__c}" /></apex:outputText> (<strong>"Interest Rate"</strong>), adjusted monthly and provided Term SOFR shall not be less than the Term SOFR Floor. Interest will be paid monthly in arrears on the tenth day of each calendar month for accrued interest for the preceding calendar month (each an <strong>"Interest Accrual Period"</strong>).  Interest will be calculated based on a 360-day year and the actual number of days elapsed (Actual/360) and will accrue on any unpaid principal balance. As used herein, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:</p>
                         <p><strong>"Interest Adjustment Date"</strong> means, for any Interest Accrual Period, the date that is two U.S. Government Securities Business Days prior to the first day of such Interest Accrual Period.</P>
                         <p><strong>"Margin"</strong> means&nbsp;<apex:outputText value="{0,number,0}%"><apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Requested_Index_Margin__c}" /></apex:outputText>.</p>
                         <p><strong>"SOFR"</strong> means a rate equal to the secured overnight financing rate as administered by the Federal Reserve Bank of New York (or a successor administrator of the secured overnight financing rate).</p>
                         <p><strong>"Term SOFR"</strong> means, for the initial Interest Accrual Period and for any subsequent Interest Accrual Period, the rate per annum equal to the forward-looking term rate based on SOFR for a one-month tenor as of the Interest Adjustment Date, as published by the CME Group Benchmark Administration Limited (or a successor administrator of such rate), as determined by Lender; provided that if as of 5:00 p.m. U.S. Central Time on any day of determination Term SOFR has not been published, then Term SOFR shall mean such rate as of the first U.S. Government Securities Business Day preceding such day of determination for which a Term SOFR was published so long as such first preceding U.S. Government Securities Business Day is not more than three U.S. Government Securities Business Days prior to such day of determination. </p>
                         <p><strong>"Term SOFR Floor"</strong> means&nbsp;<apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Requested_Index_Floor__c}" /> per annum.</p>
                         <p><strong>"U.S. Government Securities Business Day"</strong> means any day except for (i) a Saturday, (ii) a Sunday or (iii) a day on which the Securities Industry and Financial Markets Association recommends that the fixed income departments of its members be closed for the entire day for purposes of trading in United States government securities.</p>
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                           Interest Rate
                           Cap Agreement:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         Prior to or contemporaneously with Loan Closing, Borrower, at its cost, shall enter into an Interest Rate Cap Agreement with a counterparty acceptable to Lender and with a Term SOFR cap strike price equal to <span class="mark">[2.0]%</span> (the "Strike Price") or such other cap strike rate designated by Lender prior to Loan closing.  The Interest Rate Protection Agreement (i) shall be in a form and substance reasonably acceptable to Lender, (ii) shall be for a period equal to the term of the Loan; provided, however, that such period may be shorter than the full term of the Loan in the event that (A) the term is not less than two years; (B) not less than thirty (30) days prior to the expiration of such term such Interest Rate Protection Agreement is renewed or replaced by a new Interest Rate Protection Agreement with a Strike Price that is the greater of (1.) 2.0% or (2.) 1.0% above the then current SOFR rate; and otherwise complying with all the requirements of the Loan Agreement; and (C) any renewed or replacement Interest Rate Protection Agreement is subject to the Collateral Assignment of Interest Rate Protection Agreement, and Borrower and Counterparty have executed such consents and acknowledgments as Lender shall reasonably request confirming same; and (iii) shall have an initial notional amount equal to the Loan Amount. 
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                           Interest Rate
                           Amortization:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                           Interest Only
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                           Origination Fee:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         <apex:outputText value="{0,number,0}%">  <apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Requested_Origination_Fee__c}"/> </apex:outputText> of the Maximum Loan Amount payable at Closing, which fee shall be fully earned and non-refundable to Borrower.
                         </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                           Exit Fee:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                           1.00% of the Maximum Loan Amount, waived if Lender or its affiliate refinances the Loan.                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        
                        <tr>
                        <td class="row-title">
                           [Minimum Interest/
                            Spread Maintenance]:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         <p>[With respect to any payment or prepayment of the outstanding principal balance of the Loan (or acceleration of the outstanding principal balance of the Loan) on or prior to the Minimum Interest Maintenance End Date, Borrower shall pay Lender an amount equal to twenty four (24) months’ interest on the Loan Amount at an estimated applicable Interest Rate, determined by Lender prior to loan closing, less the aggregate amount of regular, monthly non-default interest that has accrued and been paid by Borrower to Lender through the date of prepayment with respect to the Loan (the “Minimum Interest Maintenance Premium”; provided that, if such prepayment occurs following an Event of Default, Borrower shall pay to Lender an amount equal to the greater of (i) the Minimum Interest Maintenance Premium, or (ii) five percent (5%) of the unpaid principal balance of the Loan as of the date of such prepayment. As used herein, “Minimum Interest Maintenance End Date” means the date Lender has received Monthly Interest Payments equal to the Minimum Interest Maintenance Premium..] [USE FOR MINIMUM INTEREST]</p>
                         <p>[With respect to any payment or prepayment of the outstanding principal balance of the Loan (or acceleration of the outstanding principal balance of the Loan) made on or prior to [______________] (the “Spread Maintenance End Date”), Borrower shall pay Lender an amount equal to the product of the following: (a) the amount of such repayment, multiplied by (b) the Margin, multiplied by (c) a fraction (expressed as a percentage) having a numerator equal to the number of days from the commencement of the next Interest Accrual Period through and including the Spread Maintenance End Date, and the denominator of which is 360 (the “Spread Maintenance Premium”); provided that, if such prepayment occurs following an Event of Default, Borrower shall pay to Lender an amount equal to the greater of (i) the Spread Maintenance Premium, or (ii) five percent (5%) of the unpaid principal balance of the Loan as of the date of such prepayment. [USE FOR SPREAD MAINTENANCE]</p>
                       </td>
                        </tr>   
                        
                        <tr>
                        <td class="row-title">
                        Extension Fee:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         0.50% of the Maximum Loan Amount payable prior to execution of each Extension
                       </td>
                        </tr>   
                        
                        <tr>
                        <td class="row-title">
                        Extension Option 
                        Requirements: 

                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                          <p>a) No default or event of default has occurred and is then continuing,</p>
                          <p>b) Borrower shall have delivered to Lender an irrevocable notice requesting such   extension at least 60 days but no more than 180 days prior to the stated maturity date,</p>
                          <p>c) Borrower shall have paid Lender the Extension Fee for each extension period and</p>
                          <p>d) The Loan must be in balance through extended maturity with Borrower depositing necessary Balancing Funds prior to the stated maturity date (see "Loan in Balance" below),</p>
                          <p>e) The Renovation Work must be Complete, including issuance of a permanent certificate of occupancy for each Residential Unit on or before the Initial Stated Maturity Date,</p>
                          <p>f) Purchase of a replacement Interest Rate Cap Agreement with a term equal to or greater than the duration of such extension on the same terms and conditions as provided in "Interest Rate Cap Agreement" above; provided that the strike price for such replacement Rate Cap shall be set such that, when added to the Interest Rate, it would result in a DSCR of at least 1.00x,</p>
                          <p>g) The Debt Yield shall be no less than [   ]% for the 1st extension and [   ]% for the 2nd extension on the effective date of such extension, based on the Property's normalized trailing twelve-month and on the most current rent roll and trailing twelve-months operating expenses from the most recent income statement, as determined by Lender,</p>
                          <p>h) The DSCR shall be no less than 1.25x for each extension, or minimum agency DSCR requirements based on the prevailing agency interest rates and amortization schedule on the effective date of such extension, as determined by Lender;</p>
                          <p>i) there has been no material adverse change in Guarantor's financial condition, as determined by Lender, and Guarantor shall have delivered to Lender a Compliance Certificate dated as of the then stated maturity date, with all supporting documentation, evidencing Guarantor is in compliance with Guarantor’s minimum liquidity and net worth covenants;</p>
                          <p>j) An LTV ratio of no greater than [  ]% as tested by an updated appraisal and </p>
                          <p>k) The Improvements must be 90% occupied at pro-forma rents.</p>
                          
                       </td>
                        </tr>  
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                        Prepayment
                        Premium:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         Provided no Event of Default is continuing, Borrower may prepay the loan at any time, in whole but not in part, provided that on or prior to such prepayment Lender shall have received thirty (30) days' prior written notice in accordance with the Loan Documents, as well as the <span class="mark">[Minimum Interest/Spread Maintenance]</span> and the Exit Fee. If such prepayment occurs on a day other than a payment date, Borrower shall also pay all interest which otherwise would have been earned on the outstanding principal balance of the Loan during the month of prepayment had the prepayment not occurred.
                       </td>
                        </tr>  
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                        Permanent
                        Financing:
                        </td>
                         <td class="row-description">
                         Although Lender shall be under no obligation to provide permanent financing, Lender shall be granted the right of first offer to provide permanent financing for the Property in accordance with products then offered by Lender and/or its affiliates. Permanent financing rights will be more specifically described in the Loan Documents. 
                       </td>
                        </tr>  
                        
                        <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                        Leasing:
